title: 471 Park Avenue. Typical plan of mezzanine or chamber floor; Typical plan of main or living room floor.

text:
Park Avenue, east side, from 58th to 59th Streets.
On the S.E. corner of 59th Street the Anderson Galleries, which later will move to 57th Street and Madison Avenue, occupy the old Arion Hall, built for the Männergesangverein Arion, or Arion Society, in 1887.
The two small garages will give place in the early 1920's to an apartment house.

June 15, 1917.

Wurts Brothers, Photographers.
